Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Finely dice @bell pepper{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1%unit}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2.5%tsp}, @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Add @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, @water{2%TBSP}, and @sugar{1%tsp}. Cook until caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, pick @green herb blend{1%unit}(leaves picked from stems and minced). Thinly slice chives.

In a second small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, minced parsley, chives, and a big pinch of remaining @garlic powder{1/2%tsp} to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread half the @sourdough bread{4%slices} with balsamic red pepper jam; sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1%cup}. Spread remaining slices with half the herb aioli (save the rest for serving). Top mozzarella with remaining slices, aioli sides down, to create sandwiches.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in pan used for jam over medium heat. Add sandwiches and cook until cheese melts and bread is golden brown, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> For 4 servings, work in batches or use a second pan. If necessary, add another drizzle of olive oil after flipping melts.

Halve melts on a diagonal. Divide between plates and serve with potatoes and remaining herb aioli on the side.